 BY ANDREW EKEJIUBA The Abia State Governor, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu has chargedfootball lovers, fans in the country and beyond to work harder in ensuring that Enyimba Football Club and Abia Warriors operate and attain the same level like their cherished football Clubs like Chelsea, Arsenal, Manchester United and the likes. Ikpeazu gave the charge at the maiden graduation ceremony ofCarl Academy And Football College located in Umuahia South LGA of Abia State. The governor represented by his Deputy, Sir Ude Oko Chukwulauded the founders for their wisdom in citing the Football Academy in Umuahia South and the State, equipping youths with academic knowledge and skills that will make them independent cum self reliant like the Education For Employment programme. He reaffirmed his administrationâ€™s support for investors willing to invest in the State, pointing out that massive road rehabilitation and infrastructural development is ongoing at every nooks and crannies of the State and appealed to the graduating students to be good ambassadors of theinstitution while more awareness should be created on the existence of the Football Academy to the outside world as well as follow up on graduating students to ensure that they excel in their chosen professions. In his speech, the Speaker of Abia State House of Assembly, Rt.Hon Chinedu Orji stressed that investing in the youths to be academically and skillfully relevant remains one of the hallmarks of development and advised theyouths to be serious with their studies in order to become responsible and champions that will do the State proud. Similarly, the Member representing Umuahia StateConstituency in the ABSHA, Chief Jerry Uzosike and the Chairman Umuahia South LGA ,Chief Humphrey Benson who thanked Governor Ikpeazu for his numerous developmentalprojects in Umuahia South and the State at large also thanked the founder ofthe institution for investing and bringing development down home. They pledged their support to the academy which will fish out future champions as well as create employment opportunities. 